1
00:01:10,060 --> 00:01:12,251
I feel such a strong connection with him.

2
00:01:12,251 --> 00:01:14,719
You'll be named All-New.

3
00:01:14,719 --> 00:01:18,622
Worth every baht I paid for your education to make you this skilled.

4
00:01:18,622 --> 00:01:20,408
We owe him hundreds of thousands.

5
00:01:20,408 --> 00:01:22,003
If we don't pay the interest tomorrow,

6
00:01:22,003 --> 00:01:22,634
we're screwed.

7
00:01:22,634 --> 00:01:24,419
Where the hell am I gonna get more money?

8
00:01:24,419 --> 00:01:26,204
Could you please consider it first?

9
00:01:26,204 --> 00:01:27,639
It doesn't really match the requirements.

10
00:01:27,639 --> 00:01:29,704
But she got the local quota, you know.

11
00:01:29,704 --> 00:01:31,331
This is about being a flight attendant, you know.

12
00:01:31,331 --> 00:01:32,646
Not enrolling in adult education.

13
00:01:32,646 --> 00:01:33,513
Why are you breaking up with me?

14
00:01:33,513 --> 00:01:35,499
Because you have no eyebrows.

15
00:01:35,499 --> 00:01:36,085
Let's break up.

16
00:01:36,085 --> 00:01:36,956
I think we should be friends instead.

17
00:01:36,956 --> 00:01:38,956
I’ll never believe in love again.

18
00:01:45,308 --> 00:01:46,730
Hello.

19
00:01:46,730 --> 00:01:48,477
Are you the one coming to intern here?

20
00:01:48,789 --> 00:01:49,789
Yes.

21
00:01:51,142 --> 00:01:53,250
What's your name? What's your zodiac sign?

22
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:59,566
My name is Srirung. "S" for Salaa, "R" for Ruea. And I'm a Leo.

23
00:01:59,566 --> 00:02:03,229
Inauspicious! Unlucky! What were they thinking giving you that name?

24
00:02:03,229 --> 00:02:05,020
My Mom named me.

25
00:02:05,020 --> 00:02:08,807
Doomed! Destined for failure! Everything you touch turns to ruin!

26
00:02:08,807 --> 00:02:11,042
Do you still want to intern here?

27
00:02:11,042 --> 00:02:11,872
Yes, I do.

28
00:02:11,872 --> 00:02:15,873
Then, you'll have to change your name.

29
00:02:15,904 --> 00:02:19,461
From now on, you'll be called Siri.

30
00:02:19,461 --> 00:02:22,486
Okay. Siri, it is.

31
00:02:22,486 --> 00:02:24,486
Excuse me.

32
00:02:32,073 --> 00:02:34,073
Miss Porn, may I?

33
00:02:37,222 --> 00:02:40,849
See? The moment you changed your name, you got a baby.

34
00:02:40,849 --> 00:02:44,117
No, I didn’t! Who would have a baby that fast?

35
00:02:44,117 --> 00:02:47,429
I caught this kid stealing from the office.

36
00:02:47,429 --> 00:02:49,427
What? Why’d you do that?

37
00:02:49,427 --> 00:02:51,093
Should we call the police?

38
00:02:51,093 --> 00:02:54,204
Whoa! Come on. He's just a kid.

39
00:02:54,204 --> 00:02:58,204
Luckily, Miss Porn forgave you.

40
00:02:58,999 --> 00:03:00,999
So? Which hand did you steal with?

41
00:03:03,469 --> 00:03:04,469
I'll cut that hand off.

42
00:03:05,382 --> 00:03:07,056
You’re really gonna cut it off?

43
00:03:07,449 --> 00:03:08,449
Just scaring him.

44
00:03:09,604 --> 00:03:11,273
Call his parents to come get him.

45
00:03:11,273 --> 00:03:12,784
I don’t have any parents.

46
00:03:12,784 --> 00:03:15,611
They left me at a temple with the monk.

47
00:03:15,611 --> 00:03:16,611
Oh…

48
00:03:18,788 --> 00:03:20,895
Then why’d you steal from here?

49
00:03:20,895 --> 00:03:22,929
I wanted the stuff to practice math.

50
00:03:22,929 --> 00:03:24,929
Show me what you took.

51
00:03:28,049 --> 00:03:29,049
Pencils

52
00:03:31,038 --> 00:03:32,038
Pens.

53
00:03:33,713 --> 00:03:34,713
A calculator.

54
00:03:37,211 --> 00:03:38,211
An abacus.

55
00:03:38,963 --> 00:03:41,148
Hey! A cash register?

56
00:03:41,148 --> 00:03:43,538
Are you going to open a conveniece store or something?

57
00:03:43,538 --> 00:03:44,966
What are you gonna do with all this?

58
00:03:44,966 --> 00:03:45,956
I like numbers.

59
00:03:45,956 --> 00:03:46,956
I want to be really good at math.

60
00:03:53,993 --> 00:03:55,706
His brows show destiny.

61
00:03:55,706 --> 00:03:57,295
His eyes show intelligence.

62
00:03:57,295 --> 00:03:58,720
His mouth shows knowledge.

63
00:03:58,720 --> 00:04:00,947
His ears show determination.

64
00:04:00,947 --> 00:04:02,412
What does that mean?

65
00:04:02,412 --> 00:04:05,000
This child is blessed.

66
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:07,871
I feel a strong connection with him.

67
00:04:07,871 --> 00:04:12,939
Alright, then. If no one's taking care of you, I will.

68
00:04:12,939 --> 00:04:15,606
You mean you're adopting me?

69
00:04:15,606 --> 00:04:20,606
Yes. If you come live with me, I’ll raise you.

70
00:04:20,883 --> 00:04:22,271
So what’s your name?

71
00:04:22,271 --> 00:04:23,466
My name’s Toon.

72
00:04:23,466 --> 00:04:25,897
What? That's not auspicious at all.

73
00:04:25,897 --> 00:04:27,814
Like the mole that lives underground?

74
00:04:27,814 --> 00:04:30,322
Okay, I’ll give you a new name.

75
00:04:30,322 --> 00:04:35,834
From now on, you’ll be called All-New.

76
00:04:35,834 --> 00:04:36,834
Thank you.

77
00:04:38,142 --> 00:04:40,207
All means everything.

78
00:04:40,207 --> 00:04:42,161
New means new.

79
00:04:42,161 --> 00:04:44,948
Together, it means everything brand new.

80
00:04:44,948 --> 00:04:46,816
That’s so chic!

81
00:04:46,816 --> 00:04:48,816
I want to be All-New’s mom too!

82
00:04:56,486 --> 00:04:58,039
How is this even possible?

83
00:04:58,039 --> 00:05:01,986
He’s only in ninth grade but can solve university-level exercises like a pro.

84
00:05:01,986 --> 00:05:03,060
Do you have any harder problems?

85
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:05,060
No, because I haven’t learned that far myself.

86
00:05:06,687 --> 00:05:09,041
How’s All-New doing?

87
00:05:09,041 --> 00:05:12,041
His IQ is now far beyond kids his age.

88
00:05:13,469 --> 00:05:14,469
That's amazing, All-New!

89
00:05:16,255 --> 00:05:18,048
By the way, what’s this?

90
00:05:18,048 --> 00:05:22,048
These are awards All-New won from global knowledge competitions.

91
00:05:22,116 --> 00:05:25,866
This one is for world-level science.

92
00:05:25,866 --> 00:05:29,866
And this one is for world-level mathematics.

93
00:05:29,897 --> 00:05:33,898
This one’s from Jittawas Phitsanulok Temple.

94
00:05:34,088 --> 00:05:35,157
How did that get here?

95
00:05:35,157 --> 00:05:36,148
That one’s mine.

96
00:05:36,148 --> 00:05:38,415
I entered a reverse chanting competition, reciting the Itipiso backwards.

97
00:05:38,415 --> 00:05:39,415
Huh?

98
00:05:40,402 --> 00:05:41,871
Wanna hear it?

99
00:05:41,871 --> 00:05:42,786
Ti-wa-ta...

100
00:05:42,786 --> 00:05:45,055
No need to show off.

101
00:05:45,055 --> 00:05:48,045
So, do you think I should study anything more?

102
00:05:48,045 --> 00:05:50,321
I think you don’t need to study anything else, All-New.

103
00:05:50,321 --> 00:05:53,113
But I want to study with you.

104
00:05:53,113 --> 00:05:54,781
Sure!

105
00:05:54,781 --> 00:05:55,781
I’ll teach you for free.

106
00:06:19,809 --> 00:06:20,809
I think I’ll take art classes instead.

107
00:06:22,396 --> 00:06:25,272
At first, he was hired to teach All-New.

108
00:06:25,272 --> 00:06:28,463
Now it’s All-New teaching him.

109
00:06:28,463 --> 00:06:32,463
Worth every baht I paid for your education to make you this skilled.

110
00:06:38,177 --> 00:06:41,809
All-New, I bought you some steamed fish.

111
00:06:41,809 --> 00:06:43,759
Whoa! Thank you so much, Siri.

112
00:06:43,759 --> 00:06:46,708
Do you ever eat anything besides fish?

113
00:06:46,708 --> 00:06:48,648
Fish has omega-3,

114
00:06:48,648 --> 00:06:49,717
phytonutrients,

115
00:06:49,717 --> 00:06:51,586
micronutrients, and minerals...

116
00:06:51,586 --> 00:06:55,587
all of which help nourish the brain and improve memory.

117
00:06:56,140 --> 00:07:00,088
Wait! Have you already been to the moon, All-New?

118
00:07:00,088 --> 00:07:02,637
Yes, I have. When I interned at NASA last month.

119
00:07:02,637 --> 00:07:04,637
Whoa, that’s so cool!

120
00:07:10,267 --> 00:07:12,063
How could it shock me?

121
00:07:12,063 --> 00:07:15,379
I installed anti-theft software.

122
00:07:16,011 --> 00:07:17,765
All-New!

123
00:07:17,765 --> 00:07:20,197
You’ve already interned at NASA?

124
00:07:20,197 --> 00:07:21,670
Yes, ma’am.

125
00:07:21,670 --> 00:07:23,946
Do you want me to intern somewhere else, Mom?

126
00:07:23,946 --> 00:07:24,973
I haven’t thought of anywhere yet.

127
00:07:24,973 --> 00:07:26,646
Then, may I go pursue further studies?

128
00:07:26,646 --> 00:07:30,361
Sure, just tell me where you want to go.

129
00:07:30,361 --> 00:07:33,518
Ooh, you look so cool in this picture, All-New!

130
00:07:33,518 --> 00:07:34,518
Don’t!

131
00:07:34,699 --> 00:07:35,699
Why not?

132
00:07:35,962 --> 00:07:38,754
Because All-New installed anti-theft software on it.

133
00:07:38,754 --> 00:07:40,068
It might shock you.

134
00:07:40,068 --> 00:07:41,068
Oh, good thing you warned me.

135
00:07:43,221 --> 00:07:45,575
Siri, that vase is really pretty.

136
00:07:45,575 --> 00:07:47,326
Did you just change it? I didn’t notice.

137
00:07:47,326 --> 00:07:48,326
Yes.

138
00:07:52,983 --> 00:07:55,176
Oh...

139
00:07:55,647 --> 00:07:59,648
All-New, you trapped the vase too?

140
00:08:00,076 --> 00:08:01,076
Yes, ma’am.

141
00:08:01,982 --> 00:08:03,172
Because at NASA...

142
00:08:03,172 --> 00:08:04,172
Security is number one.

143
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:13,240
All-New, how about a haircut, sweetie?

144
00:08:14,830 --> 00:08:15,830
It’s covering your whole face now.

145
00:08:22,220 --> 00:08:23,220
Ready?

146
00:08:23,496 --> 00:08:25,496
One, two, three.

147
00:08:27,485 --> 00:08:30,997
Here you go, Mom. First-class honors degree from Hartvard.

148
00:08:30,997 --> 00:08:32,545
Still want me to keep studying here?

149
00:08:32,545 --> 00:08:34,453
Whoa! Enough already.

150
00:08:34,453 --> 00:08:36,453
Look at what we got here...

151
00:08:40,127 --> 00:08:42,037
I’m really proud of you.

152
00:08:42,037 --> 00:08:45,391
Totally worth every baht I spent on your education.

153
00:08:45,391 --> 00:08:47,945
Then how about I build an airplane instead?

154
00:08:47,945 --> 00:08:48,694
Huh?

155
00:08:48,694 --> 00:08:49,964
Can you do that?

156
00:08:49,964 --> 00:08:51,479
I’ve already thought it all through.

157
00:08:51,479 --> 00:08:55,231
If we count the design and the manufacturing process,

158
00:08:55,231 --> 00:08:57,577
it should take around...

159
00:08:57,577 --> 00:08:58,577
forty years.

160
00:09:01,237 --> 00:09:03,590
Too long. Easier to just buy one.

161
00:09:03,590 --> 00:09:06,025
But I want it to be the best.

162
00:09:06,025 --> 00:09:10,025
Madam, are you planning to send All-New to study anywhere else?

163
00:09:10,174 --> 00:09:16,174
No, I’m going to have All-New work at Porn Airline.

164
00:09:16,883 --> 00:09:18,751
Sure, Mom.

165
00:09:18,751 --> 00:09:21,419
And stop calling me Mom.

166
00:09:21,419 --> 00:09:22,375
Why not?

167
00:09:22,375 --> 00:09:25,273
Because if the other staff find out, it won’t look good.

168
00:09:25,273 --> 00:09:27,340
They’ll say I hired my own son.

169
00:09:27,340 --> 00:09:29,814
So if I can’t call you Mom, what should I call you?

170
00:09:29,814 --> 00:09:33,121
Call me like everyone else does.

171
00:09:33,121 --> 00:09:34,121
Bitchy Madam Porn.

172
00:09:35,986 --> 00:09:38,979
That’s what I heard Siri and the others call you.

173
00:09:38,979 --> 00:09:42,979
Are you crazy, All-New? Who would dare call her that?

174
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:48,332
She’s the boss! We gotta watch our mouths!

175
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:55,031
From now on, you follow only my orders.

176
00:09:55,031 --> 00:09:56,177
Yes, Mom.

177
00:09:56,177 --> 00:09:58,570
I said stop calling me Mom!

178
00:09:58,570 --> 00:10:00,886
But I’ve always called you that. Let me keep doing it, please.

179
00:10:00,886 --> 00:10:03,954
Are you being defiant, All-New? Siri, bring me the stick.

180
00:10:03,954 --> 00:10:05,421
What’s going on, Madam?

181
00:10:05,421 --> 00:10:07,572
All-New’s being stubborn. He needs a little lesson!

182
00:10:07,572 --> 00:10:08,846
Mom, please don’t hurt me.

183
00:10:08,846 --> 00:10:12,847
Stop calling me Mom. Stop it! Stop it!

184
00:10:15,915 --> 00:10:16,747
Oh! Okay!

185
00:10:16,747 --> 00:10:17,694
Are you gonna call me that again?

186
00:10:17,694 --> 00:10:19,205
Madam Porn! Madam Porn!

187
00:10:19,205 --> 00:10:20,205
There. See?

188
00:10:22,839 --> 00:10:23,839
Sometimes you just need force.

189
00:10:24,585 --> 00:10:25,585
Excuse me now, Mom.

190
00:10:26,101 --> 00:10:28,251
I said don’t call me Mom!

191
00:10:28,493 --> 00:10:30,643
Come here, come here!

192
00:10:30,643 --> 00:10:32,643
Are you gonna stop calling me that?

193
00:10:37,714 --> 00:10:39,062
Hey, you know what?

194
00:10:39,062 --> 00:10:41,534
Honestly, folding paper bags…it’s actually kinda easy.

195
00:10:41,534 --> 00:10:45,452
You can do it at home, no need to go anywhere.

196
00:10:45,452 --> 00:10:48,528
But four bags only get you one baht?

197
00:10:48,528 --> 00:10:52,036
Yeah, but forty bags is ten baht.

198
00:10:52,036 --> 00:10:54,273
Four thousand bags is a thousand baht, dude.

199
00:10:54,273 --> 00:10:55,543
And four million bags?

200
00:10:55,543 --> 00:10:57,489
That’s a million baht, bro!

201
00:10:57,489 --> 00:10:59,163
I’ve been folding all day, my hands are cramping...

202
00:10:59,163 --> 00:11:00,831
and I only got through two hundred bags.

203
00:11:00,831 --> 00:11:01,783
That’s still pretty good.

204
00:11:01,783 --> 00:11:03,250
You made fifty baht already.

205
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:05,277
If I had to fold four million bags,

206
00:11:05,587 --> 00:11:09,417
I’d be dead before I ever get to spend that money.

207
00:11:09,417 --> 00:11:11,933
Kreetha, where the hell were you last night?

208
00:11:11,933 --> 00:11:15,440
Oh, I was working a catering gig for a Chinese banquet, Dad.

209
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:19,440
Made three hundred baht!

210
00:11:23,871 --> 00:11:25,520
That’s the spirit, boy!

211
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:27,992
But I’m saving that money for Mom’s hospital visit.

212
00:11:27,992 --> 00:11:30,980
Is that little bit even enough to cover her treatment?

213
00:11:30,980 --> 00:11:33,012
We need more.

214
00:11:33,012 --> 00:11:37,012
After I’m done with the cockfight, I’ll take your Mom to the doctor myself.

215
00:11:39,278 --> 00:11:42,926
Yes! You finally get to fight!

216
00:11:42,926 --> 00:11:44,926
Let’s go. Let’s go!

217
00:11:46,513 --> 00:11:48,146
So, are all your family’s debts paid off yet?

218
00:11:48,146 --> 00:11:49,135
Not even close.

219
00:11:49,135 --> 00:11:50,965
Your Dad’s a gambling addict,

220
00:11:50,965 --> 00:11:52,876
and your Mom’s sick.

221
00:11:52,876 --> 00:11:54,745
When the hell are you ever gonna be debt-free?

222
00:11:54,745 --> 00:11:55,894
I don’t know, man.

223
00:11:55,894 --> 00:11:57,894
But I just wanna find a way to make more money.

224
00:12:06,041 --> 00:12:08,717
Kree…dude…

225
00:12:09,592 --> 00:12:11,987
Tong, are you feeling sorry for me or something, bro?

226
00:12:11,987 --> 00:12:14,219
Your Dad took fifty baht from me.

227
00:12:14,219 --> 00:12:15,046
What the...

228
00:12:15,046 --> 00:12:16,762
Man, I folded two hundred bags all day,

229
00:12:16,762 --> 00:12:18,992
and now it was all for nothing!

230
00:12:18,992 --> 00:12:20,740
Tong, I…I’m sorry, bro.

231
00:12:20,740 --> 00:12:23,967
Your family’s a bunch of…scammers.

232
00:12:23,967 --> 00:12:25,518
I’ll pay you back.

233
00:12:25,518 --> 00:12:27,518
But right now, I have no idea how to get the money.

234
00:12:30,271 --> 00:12:32,781
You know how to box? I’ve got a job for you.

235
00:12:32,781 --> 00:12:33,528
How much?

236
00:12:33,528 --> 00:12:34,241
Tens of thousands.

237
00:12:34,241 --> 00:12:36,951
What? Tens of thousands?

238
00:12:36,951 --> 00:12:40,140
But man…I don’t know how to fight.

239
00:12:40,140 --> 00:12:43,011
Don’t worry. The other guy’s gonna throw the match.

240
00:12:43,011 --> 00:12:45,011
You just gotta throw a few punches and fake it.

241
00:12:54,166 --> 00:12:58,166
Dude, you were amazing! So damn convincing, they totally bought it.

242
00:12:58,197 --> 00:13:00,106
What the hell? You said the other guy would throw the fight!

243
00:13:00,106 --> 00:13:02,106
Look at my face, man!

244
00:13:04,292 --> 00:13:06,925
You needed to take a few hits so it’d look real!

245
00:13:06,925 --> 00:13:10,003
Dude, I don’t even recognize myself right now!

246
00:13:10,003 --> 00:13:12,272
Tong! Where’s Kreetha?

247
00:13:12,272 --> 00:13:14,064
Right here, Dad.

248
00:13:14,064 --> 00:13:16,173
What the hell happened to you?

249
00:13:16,173 --> 00:13:19,964
He went boxing. He killed it. He scored ten thousand baht.

250
00:13:19,964 --> 00:13:22,796
Ten thousand? Damn!

251
00:13:22,796 --> 00:13:28,796
Here, Dad, use this money to pay off our debt to Mr. Berm so we can be done with this.

252
00:13:31,045 --> 00:13:33,642
You're such a good son.

253
00:13:33,642 --> 00:13:35,642
I’m proud of you.

254
00:13:36,919 --> 00:13:39,026
But did you forget something?

255
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:40,331
Forget what?

256
00:13:40,331 --> 00:13:42,960
We owe him a hundred thousand.

257
00:13:42,960 --> 00:13:45,353
That ten grand?

258
00:13:45,353 --> 00:13:47,140
It’s not even enough to cover the interest.

259
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:48,255
So what now?

260
00:13:48,255 --> 00:13:52,255
We go hustle more, obviously!

261
00:13:52,683 --> 00:13:54,683
Why are you still asking me that?

262
00:13:57,393 --> 00:14:01,464
It's okay, sweetie. It's not cold.

263
00:14:01,464 --> 00:14:03,090
Wait, no, it's the phone ringing

264
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:04,090
Jeez!

265
00:14:08,002 --> 00:14:09,002
Yes, Mr. Berm?

266
00:14:11,232 --> 00:14:12,732
Yes, sir. Got it.

267
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:14,460
I’ll take care of it tomorrow.

268
00:14:16,128 --> 00:14:17,128
Was that Mr. Berm?

269
00:14:17,436 --> 00:14:18,436
Yes.

270
00:14:18,501 --> 00:14:22,501
He said if we don’t pay the interest tomorrow...

271
00:14:23,609 --> 00:14:24,609
we’re screwed.

272
00:14:24,917 --> 00:14:28,667
I’ll go borrow money from someone else first.

273
00:14:28,667 --> 00:14:30,667
Let’s go, sweetie. Let’s go!

274
00:14:32,696 --> 00:14:35,164
Wish me luck. I hope my begging works out.

275
00:14:35,164 --> 00:14:38,154
Honestly...

276
00:14:38,154 --> 00:14:40,703
your family’s never getting out of debt in this lifetime.

277
00:14:40,703 --> 00:14:44,657
Then where the hell am I supposed to find more money?

278
00:14:44,657 --> 00:14:47,245
I’ve got an auntie who sells stuff at the market.

279
00:14:47,641 --> 00:14:50,432
She said frogs are going for a good price right now.

280
00:14:50,432 --> 00:14:52,787
I’ll take you frog hunting.

281
00:14:52,787 --> 00:14:55,657
Frog hunting? What’s that?

282
00:14:55,657 --> 00:15:00,157
Frog hunting is when you strap a flashlight to your head,

283
00:15:00,445 --> 00:15:04,446
and there’s a pair of frogs, getting it on legally in the middle of a rice field.

284
00:15:04,834 --> 00:15:08,383
That’s peak season, when frogs come out for you to catch.

285
00:15:08,383 --> 00:15:11,979
Hey, that’s not a bad idea. It doesn’t cost much to start.

286
00:15:11,979 --> 00:15:13,979
When you shine your light, the frog will just freeze like this.

287
00:15:21,406 --> 00:15:23,597
We hunted frogs all night and only made 500 baht.

288
00:15:23,597 --> 00:15:26,433
At this rate, when are you ever gonna be the first in line like them?

289
00:15:26,433 --> 00:15:29,062
I'm pretty sure I should be asking you that.

290
00:15:29,062 --> 00:15:31,013
Damn...thanks, man.

291
00:15:31,013 --> 00:15:32,996
I didn’t give it to you. It’s a loan.

292
00:15:32,996 --> 00:15:35,710
You owe me 550 including your dad’s cut too.

293
00:15:35,710 --> 00:15:36,893
Thanks a lot, bro.

294
00:15:36,893 --> 00:15:37,893
He's here, he's here.

295
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:40,191
Hey! Where’ve you guys been?

296
00:15:40,191 --> 00:15:42,425
We went frog hunting, Dad.

297
00:15:42,425 --> 00:15:44,425
We didn’t make much money but at least we’ve got frogs to eat.

298
00:15:49,401 --> 00:15:51,914
But we seriously need to find cash fast.

299
00:15:51,914 --> 00:15:55,305
I've been borrowing from one person to pay off another.

300
00:15:55,305 --> 00:15:58,652
I borrowed from Auntie Aeow, paid off Moo...it’s a mess.

301
00:15:58,652 --> 00:16:01,602
Now, I can’t even remember who I owe.

302
00:16:01,602 --> 00:16:02,830
What does that mean, Dad?

303
00:16:02,830 --> 00:16:05,180
It means we all gotta help find money.

304
00:16:05,180 --> 00:16:07,569
We owe the whole damn village by now.

305
00:16:07,569 --> 00:16:10,639
Can you get back in the ring for another boxing match?

306
00:16:10,639 --> 00:16:13,467
They already shut the gym down.

307
00:16:13,467 --> 00:16:17,467
If we can’t pay, then let the bank take the house.

308
00:16:17,653 --> 00:16:18,879
I’ll help find money, Dad.

309
00:16:18,879 --> 00:16:22,626
Okay. I’ll take your mom to the hospital first.

310
00:16:22,626 --> 00:16:23,855
What’s wrong with her?

311
00:16:23,855 --> 00:16:26,047
She’s married to me, that’s what’s wrong.

312
00:16:26,047 --> 00:16:28,278
You little...say one more word and the rooster’s pecking your face!

313
00:16:28,278 --> 00:16:29,832
I mean, what sickness does she have?

314
00:16:29,832 --> 00:16:33,832
Probably diabetes. If you wanna know, go ask your Mom.

315
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:38,820
Go on, go! Look at you, shaking like you want a beating.

316
00:16:38,957 --> 00:16:42,370
Peck his eyes out, will you? Let's go.

317
00:16:42,370 --> 00:16:45,967
Didn’t you ever teach your Dad any manners?

318
00:16:45,967 --> 00:16:47,881
Only have a Dad when you're ready.

319
00:16:47,881 --> 00:16:49,881
How the hell am I supposed to make tens of thousands now?

320
00:16:52,430 --> 00:16:53,663
There is a way.

321
00:16:53,663 --> 00:16:54,728
Dude, are you secretly working at the Labor Ministry or something?

322
00:16:54,728 --> 00:16:56,519
You always got new jobs popping up.

323
00:16:56,519 --> 00:16:59,780
There’s a temple fair today. They’re holding a lion dance competition.

324
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,492
300,000 baht. first prize.

325
00:17:01,492 --> 00:17:05,492
If we win, we’ll walk away with no less than five digits.

326
00:17:05,967 --> 00:17:07,475
But I don’t know how to lion dance, man!

327
00:17:07,475 --> 00:17:11,475
Dude, that team’s already solid.

328
00:17:11,543 --> 00:17:13,532
Nine-time reigning champs.

329
00:17:13,532 --> 00:17:15,036
We just have to join the dance.

330
00:17:15,036 --> 00:17:16,036
Finish the routine, that’s it.

331
00:17:22,989 --> 00:17:25,497
That was so close.

332
00:17:25,497 --> 00:17:27,049
We just missed it by that much.

333
00:17:27,049 --> 00:17:29,233
Dude, you said the dance was easy!

334
00:17:29,233 --> 00:17:31,511
Good thing I know how to tuck my neck in.

335
00:17:31,511 --> 00:17:33,736
That’s you with neck control?

336
00:17:33,736 --> 00:17:36,364
What would it have looked like without it?

337
00:17:36,364 --> 00:17:39,234
You’re the one who tricked me into doing it!

338
00:17:39,234 --> 00:17:42,782
How was I supposed to know they were missing the top guy?

339
00:17:42,782 --> 00:17:44,134
I didn't think it would be that high.

340
00:17:44,134 --> 00:17:48,135
Damn you! That was like an eight-story building, as tall as power lines!

341
00:17:48,333 --> 00:17:50,333
Come on. At least you didn’t die.

342
00:17:59,283 --> 00:18:00,953
Where are you going, Dad?

343
00:18:00,953 --> 00:18:03,825
How can I stay? The debt collectors called.

344
00:18:03,825 --> 00:18:06,013
They threatened to kill me and your Mom.

345
00:18:06,013 --> 00:18:07,007
Huh?

346
00:18:07,007 --> 00:18:08,635
No “huh”s.

347
00:18:08,635 --> 00:18:11,984
I think we need to go lay low at Uncle Nun’s place.

348
00:18:11,984 --> 00:18:12,935
He’s our relative.

349
00:18:12,935 --> 00:18:13,643
And Mom?

350
00:18:13,643 --> 00:18:17,643
I’ll go pick her up from the hospital, and we’ll escape together.

351
00:18:18,116 --> 00:18:19,351
Kai-tom, calm down.

352
00:18:19,351 --> 00:18:21,824
But Dad, what about this house?

353
00:18:22,147 --> 00:18:24,615
Still worried about the house? Let them take it.

354
00:18:24,615 --> 00:18:26,888
Call me if anything happens.

355
00:18:26,888 --> 00:18:29,888
I’ll go wait at Uncle Nun’s place.

356
00:18:31,284 --> 00:18:34,036
Calm down, sweetie. We’re not leaving you.

357
00:18:34,036 --> 00:18:36,025
Scratch this kid’s eye out for me, will you?

358
00:18:36,025 --> 00:18:39,134
Bro, I’m seriously confused.

359
00:18:39,134 --> 00:18:40,881
What is your family dynamic?

360
00:18:40,881 --> 00:18:42,598
Forget it. I’m used to it.

361
00:18:42,598 --> 00:18:45,226
You’re used to this? When are you ever gonna be the first in line?

362
00:18:45,226 --> 00:18:46,499
When’s your turn to get rich, huh?

363
00:18:46,499 --> 00:18:50,499
I gotta stay behind and pay off my parents’ debt. What else can I do?

364
00:18:52,211 --> 00:18:53,602
I know a brothel run by Uncle Song...

365
00:18:53,602 --> 00:18:56,389
Stop it, Tong! Enough already!

366
00:18:56,389 --> 00:19:00,389
I’m heading to Bangkok to find a job and start saving.

367
00:19:17,007 --> 00:19:18,995
Chaba!

368
00:19:18,995 --> 00:19:19,822
What are you doing?

369
00:19:19,822 --> 00:19:21,822
Oh hey, Sky!

370
00:19:23,099 --> 00:19:26,010
I'm answering a health advice column right now.

371
00:19:26,010 --> 00:19:28,800
Whoa, you're a health guru now?

372
00:19:28,800 --> 00:19:31,109
Yup, I’m based in the “Kitchen Corner” section.

373
00:19:31,109 --> 00:19:32,896
See this?

374
00:19:32,896 --> 00:19:36,321
Whoa! That’s the newest Blackberry model!

375
00:19:36,321 --> 00:19:38,233
How’d you even get that?

376
00:19:38,233 --> 00:19:41,700
You know, just the usual. Life’s gotta stay updated.

377
00:19:41,700 --> 00:19:42,406
So fancy.

378
00:19:42,406 --> 00:19:44,602
And...

379
00:19:44,602 --> 00:19:48,114
Hey! That’s a Mosquito leather bag!

380
00:19:48,114 --> 00:19:50,667
With reverse stitching!

381
00:19:50,667 --> 00:19:52,612
Sky, you're super high-society!

382
00:19:52,612 --> 00:19:55,520
Anyway, Chaba, I need your advice.

383
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:59,275
Someone called me. They want to feature me in Caesar magazine.

384
00:19:59,275 --> 00:20:02,188
Wait, Caesar magazine?

385
00:20:02,188 --> 00:20:07,177
The one that features all the cool, cute, chic people?

386
00:20:07,177 --> 00:20:10,574
Yep, that one. But...

387
00:20:10,574 --> 00:20:11,970
I’ve got a small issue.

388
00:20:11,970 --> 00:20:15,765
I can’t think of a good pose right now.

389
00:20:15,765 --> 00:20:19,038
Why don’t you check out Dek-D’s website?

390
00:20:19,038 --> 00:20:22,826
Like the ones Balloon or Bebe did, super cute stuff.

391
00:20:22,826 --> 00:20:25,093
I don’t wanna be like them.

392
00:20:25,093 --> 00:20:28,248
Okay, then what now?

393
00:20:28,248 --> 00:20:30,241
Maybe just try out a few poses and see what works?

394
00:20:30,241 --> 00:20:31,236
You want me to help?

395
00:20:31,236 --> 00:20:32,236
Yeah, okay!

396
00:20:37,349 --> 00:20:41,349
Sky, that’s terrifying. Not this one.

397
00:20:41,775 --> 00:20:42,604
Really?

398
00:20:42,604 --> 00:20:43,604
Yeah.

399
00:20:46,121 --> 00:20:50,122
Whoa, been drowning or something?

400
00:20:50,908 --> 00:20:52,944
No! That’s the cutesy pose everyone’s doing! I saw it on Hi5.

401
00:20:52,944 --> 00:20:55,214
Ohh, the chipmunk cheeks pose?

402
00:20:55,214 --> 00:20:55,921
Yeah!

403
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:57,908
It’s actually really cute, that one.

404
00:20:57,908 --> 00:21:00,344
How about this?

405
00:21:00,344 --> 00:21:01,376
Are you okay?

406
00:21:01,376 --> 00:21:02,765
That’s me being cute!

407
00:21:02,765 --> 00:21:06,766
I think it’s equal parts adorable and terrifying.

408
00:21:07,668 --> 00:21:09,668
I say stick with the chipmunk cheeks.

409
00:21:13,022 --> 00:21:17,022
Sky! My bag and phone...where are they?

410
00:21:17,771 --> 00:21:18,771
Hurry up!

411
00:21:20,886 --> 00:21:22,955
I told you to watch the table!

412
00:21:22,955 --> 00:21:24,955
Why are you even here?

413
00:21:25,944 --> 00:21:27,944
I had to pee so I stopped by to say hi.

414
00:21:28,381 --> 00:21:29,381
That was a long pee.

415
00:21:33,171 --> 00:21:37,172
Sky, don’t tell me you borrowed that stuff just to flex?

416
00:21:41,682 --> 00:21:43,905
Don’t tell anyone, okay?

417
00:21:43,905 --> 00:21:47,213
She rented my bag and my Blackberry just to take Hi5 pics.

418
00:21:47,213 --> 00:21:49,880
What? Seriously?

419
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:52,746
I thought, someone as posh as Sky,

420
00:21:52,746 --> 00:21:56,698
with that skin and face...no way she stole that stuff.

421
00:21:56,698 --> 00:21:59,284
Just lucky I’ve got sponsor parents.

422
00:21:59,284 --> 00:22:00,284
So in the end...

423
00:22:03,026 --> 00:22:04,026
So tasty.

424
00:22:07,373 --> 00:22:08,373
Hello, Dad.

425
00:22:11,043 --> 00:22:13,029
Don’t worry.

426
00:22:13,029 --> 00:22:15,029
Once I graduate, I’ll come back and climb for bird’s nests.

427
00:22:17,187 --> 00:22:19,187
Let me gain some knowledge first.

428
00:22:20,731 --> 00:22:21,731
I’m worried, Dad.

429
00:22:22,966 --> 00:22:23,966
Sky, who are you talking to?

430
00:22:28,554 --> 00:22:29,703
I’m talking to my Dad.

431
00:22:29,703 --> 00:22:33,703
Wait, didn’t you say your dad lives in the Netherlands?

432
00:22:33,737 --> 00:22:36,325
That accent is super Southern though.

433
00:22:36,325 --> 00:22:37,325
He’s my godfather.

434
00:22:41,677 --> 00:22:42,677
Hello, Dad.

435
00:22:43,950 --> 00:22:45,950
Once the semester ends, I’ll hurry and take the train home.

436
00:22:47,338 --> 00:22:48,338
Yes.

437
00:22:48,809 --> 00:22:49,809
Yes, Dad. Goodbye.

438
00:22:50,276 --> 00:22:52,027
What did your Dad say, Nui? (Southern accent)

439
00:22:52,027 --> 00:22:54,735
He told me to come home. (Southern accent)

440
00:22:54,735 --> 00:22:57,000
See? Liar.

441
00:22:57,000 --> 00:22:59,272
Such a fake high-society wannabe.

442
00:22:59,272 --> 00:23:01,272
So what?

443
00:23:03,743 --> 00:23:04,743
Whoa.

444
00:23:05,909 --> 00:23:06,909
What?

445
00:23:07,253 --> 00:23:08,643
What are you sitting on?

446
00:23:08,643 --> 00:23:09,558
It’s nothing.

447
00:23:09,558 --> 00:23:11,429
Is that the latest bean bag model or what?

448
00:23:11,429 --> 00:23:12,415
What?

449
00:23:12,415 --> 00:23:13,729
It’s just snacks.

450
00:23:13,729 --> 00:23:16,077
I bought them to try. What's the big deal?

451
00:23:16,077 --> 00:23:21,868
Oh, answering health questions for the website, huh?

452
00:23:21,868 --> 00:23:24,652
But eating that many crunchy snacks...

453
00:23:24,652 --> 00:23:27,409
Isn’t that misleading your followers a bit?

454
00:23:27,409 --> 00:23:29,524
Why? You’re just as fake as I am.

455
00:23:29,524 --> 00:23:31,037
You’re fake too.

456
00:23:31,037 --> 00:23:33,985
But I’m not pretending to be some rich fancy girl.

457
00:23:33,985 --> 00:23:36,581
But if I expose you...

458
00:23:36,581 --> 00:23:40,581
show them your real self, like a water buffalo...

459
00:23:41,054 --> 00:23:44,080
how are you gonna survive the internet, huh?

460
00:23:44,080 --> 00:23:49,029
And what if I expose you for using a coconut shell as a phone to call home?

461
00:23:49,029 --> 00:23:52,418
Wouldn’t you be embarrassed, “high-society Sky”?

462
00:23:52,418 --> 00:23:56,165
What if I post your real photo on Hi5

463
00:23:56,165 --> 00:23:57,476
and spill everything about you?

464
00:23:57,476 --> 00:24:03,069
Your fans would come for you so hard, you’d have no place left online.

465
00:24:03,069 --> 00:24:07,739
Then, I’d apologize, people would pity me and forgive me.

466
00:24:07,739 --> 00:24:10,544
But you, acting rich when you’re actually broke...

467
00:24:10,544 --> 00:24:12,617
Enough. You wanna fight?

468
00:24:12,617 --> 00:24:13,444
Come on, hit me first.

469
00:24:13,444 --> 00:24:13,844
You hit me first.

470
00:24:14,233 --> 00:24:14,633
You hit me first.

471
00:24:15,142 --> 00:24:16,096
I’m letting you hit me first.

472
00:24:16,096 --> 00:24:17,654
Well then, you go first. I’m letting you too.

473
00:24:17,654 --> 00:24:18,561
I wanna get slapped by a rich girl.

474
00:24:18,561 --> 00:24:19,747
So what if my friend’s high-society?

475
00:24:19,747 --> 00:24:20,618
But don’t make me talk.

476
00:24:20,618 --> 00:24:21,643
Don’t make me talk either.

477
00:24:21,643 --> 00:24:22,677
If I expose you, you’re done.

478
00:24:22,677 --> 00:24:24,753
Same to you. Do it!

479
00:24:24,753 --> 00:24:25,708
I’ll post on Hi5.

480
00:24:25,708 --> 00:24:27,061
I’ll post everything. But don’t make me talk.

481
00:24:27,061 --> 00:24:27,929
I’ll post on Dek-D too.

482
00:24:27,929 --> 00:24:28,598
I’ll post on Dek-D first.

483
00:24:28,598 --> 00:24:29,674
What now? Wanna fight?

484
00:24:29,674 --> 00:24:30,539
Then I won’t talk.

485
00:24:30,539 --> 00:24:31,964
Then I won’t talk either.

486
00:24:31,964 --> 00:24:33,722
Okay, it’s over.

487
00:24:33,722 --> 00:24:34,517
Alright then.

488
00:24:34,517 --> 00:24:35,591
Let’s not fight anymore.

489
00:24:35,591 --> 00:24:36,388
Yeah.

490
00:24:36,388 --> 00:24:40,388
Yeah, come to think of it, we know way too many secrets about each other.

491
00:24:41,058 --> 00:24:43,125
So maybe we should be best friends instead.

492
00:24:43,125 --> 00:24:45,633
Honestly, we’re kind of meant to be friends.

493
00:24:45,633 --> 00:24:49,633
We’re on the same level. Both two-faced liars.

494
00:24:50,146 --> 00:24:51,136
Let’s be friends.

495
00:24:51,136 --> 00:24:52,136
Deal.

496
00:24:53,327 --> 00:24:57,041
And about the secrets, if I don’t say anything, you don’t say anything.

497
00:24:57,041 --> 00:24:59,949
We’ll keep it a secret forever. Deal?

498
00:24:59,949 --> 00:25:01,940
Best friends forever.

499
00:25:01,940 --> 00:25:02,940
Promise.

500
00:25:05,681 --> 00:25:08,675
Massage! Thai massage!

501
00:25:08,675 --> 00:25:10,142
This way, please. We do every style.

502
00:25:10,142 --> 00:25:12,570
Thai massage! Thai massage!

503
00:25:12,570 --> 00:25:14,404
Thai massage!

504
00:25:14,404 --> 00:25:18,404
Thai massage, very relaxing!

505
00:25:20,350 --> 00:25:21,350
Excuse me.

506
00:25:24,104 --> 00:25:25,934
Would you like a massage?

507
00:25:25,934 --> 00:25:27,723
We’ve got lots of packages.

508
00:25:28,517 --> 00:25:29,517
Hmm…no, thank you.

509
00:25:30,390 --> 00:25:34,390
Oh, come on. Just give it a try.

510
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:37,900
We’ve got special massage too.

511
00:25:39,571 --> 00:25:40,571
Special massage?

512
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:44,119
I mean Thai-style...additional style.

513
00:25:44,119 --> 00:25:47,095
We’ve got international styles too.

514
00:25:47,095 --> 00:25:53,095
Or maybe a four-hand massage, two on one?

515
00:25:54,889 --> 00:25:55,889
No, thank you.

516
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:02,069
Wait a sec, Sky. Isn’t our shop supposed to be all about health massage?

517
00:26:02,069 --> 00:26:04,978
So what? Gotta sneak in some spicy service now and then.

518
00:26:04,978 --> 00:26:06,445
The owner has no clue...

519
00:26:06,445 --> 00:26:08,395
She’s too busy getting her nails and following her husband's mistress.

520
00:26:08,395 --> 00:26:09,395
True that.

