780
00:39:53,390 --> 00:39:54,390
It was amazing.

781
00:39:56,735 --> 00:40:00,735
Tid-Gift…I think we should be a couple.

782
00:40:13,611 --> 00:40:14,611
Wait, I need to take this call.

783
00:40:20,906 --> 00:40:21,906
Hang on, babe.

784
00:40:26,820 --> 00:40:27,820
Hello?

785
00:40:28,369 --> 00:40:29,369
I should write this in my diary.

786
00:40:32,083 --> 00:40:33,083
King…

787
00:40:34,238 --> 00:40:41,110
King is like a prince on a white horse, riding straight into my heart.

788
00:40:41,110 --> 00:40:50,110
From now on, it’s just the two of us. We’ll live for each other.

789
00:40:51,494 --> 00:40:52,494
What’s up?

790
00:40:53,322 --> 00:40:55,322
I’m with my girlfriend right now. And she’s hot.

791
00:40:57,241 --> 00:40:58,241
Huh?

792
00:40:59,827 --> 00:41:00,827
Really?

793
00:41:02,178 --> 00:41:03,178
Yeah, for sure.

794
00:41:04,851 --> 00:41:05,851
Tid-Gift…

795
00:41:06,399 --> 00:41:07,399
Let’s break up.

796
00:41:08,908 --> 00:41:09,908
What?

797
00:41:10,015 --> 00:41:11,693
We’ve only been a couple for, like, a minute!

798
00:41:11,693 --> 00:41:12,693
Well, my ex just called to patch things up.

799
00:41:13,280 --> 00:41:14,280
And…we’re back together now.

800
00:41:15,714 --> 00:41:16,714
I have to go back to her.

801
00:41:18,140 --> 00:41:19,487
What?

802
00:41:19,487 --> 00:41:23,487
Then let’s say this, you’re too good for me. We don’t match.

803
00:41:23,558 --> 00:41:26,558
Maybe we’ll run into each other again…but who knows...

804
00:41:28,424 --> 00:41:29,424
Bye-bye.

805
00:41:31,615 --> 00:41:32,615
Did he just do that to me?

806
00:41:36,526 --> 00:41:40,526
Boy is my warm and rosy world.

807
00:41:41,875 --> 00:41:45,623
He’s the one who completes my dream of love.

808
00:41:45,623 --> 00:41:48,770
Today, I’m so happy we’re together.

809
00:41:48,770 --> 00:41:52,770
My love feels so sweet and full of bliss.

810
00:41:57,832 --> 00:41:59,588
Boy…what’s wrong?

811
00:41:59,588 --> 00:42:01,497
Tid-Gift…I had a terrible nightmare.

812
00:42:01,497 --> 00:42:04,367
I dreamed that my ex, who passed away, came to snap my neck.

813
00:42:04,367 --> 00:42:07,040
I think we should be friends instead. I gotta go now.

814
00:42:07,040 --> 00:42:09,040
Wait, it’s raining!

815
00:42:12,774 --> 00:42:14,774
Even the sky is crying for me!

816
00:42:16,845 --> 00:42:19,845
Why can’t you feel even a little sympathy for me, Boy?

817
00:42:27,001 --> 00:42:30,472
Tod is a beautiful kind of love.

818
00:42:30,472 --> 00:42:33,661
His gentleness is truly precious.

819
00:42:33,661 --> 00:42:36,818
Every moment near him brings me joy.

820
00:42:36,818 --> 00:42:40,818
And every touch brings me peace.

821
00:42:43,084 --> 00:42:45,084
Tid-Gift, I’m heading to the club meeting now, okay?

822
00:42:52,437 --> 00:42:56,437
Oh, Magical Little Bear…I’m just so happy.

823
00:43:05,785 --> 00:43:06,785
My money!

824
00:43:15,340 --> 00:43:17,340
That damn Tod hung up on me!

825
00:43:19,931 --> 00:43:21,931
and stole my money!

826
00:43:27,640 --> 00:43:31,591
I'm heartbroken...

827
00:43:31,591 --> 00:43:34,591
Gotta play some breakup music.

828
00:43:36,985 --> 00:43:40,986
"You taught me to understand...

829
00:43:42,738 --> 00:43:46,738
that bonds can’t buy love."

830
00:43:48,850 --> 00:43:50,758
I gotta change the station.

831
00:43:50,758 --> 00:43:51,758
"Not the one that you..."

832
00:43:53,239 --> 00:43:55,264
"Back then, I had you. Back then, I had you."

833
00:43:55,264 --> 00:43:58,051
"Once, I used to have you. I used to have you."

834
00:43:58,051 --> 00:44:02,051
"But now I don’t. I don’t have you anymore."

835
00:44:02,120 --> 00:44:04,985
Love is cruel.

836
00:44:04,985 --> 00:44:08,336
Love is brutal to me.

837
00:44:08,336 --> 00:44:11,807
How could he do that to me?

838
00:44:11,807 --> 00:44:13,876
From now on…

839
00:44:13,876 --> 00:44:15,876
I will never believe in love again.

840
00:44:23,380 --> 00:44:28,380
The concept of organizational change...

841
00:44:34,490 --> 00:44:36,361
You’ve really changed, Tid-Gift.

842
00:44:36,361 --> 00:44:39,361
Well, people grow from experience, you know.

843
00:44:41,033 --> 00:44:45,033
In that case…I don’t think we can keep being friends.

844
00:44:45,261 --> 00:44:47,261
My mom only wants me to be friends with “proper” girls.

845
00:44:48,931 --> 00:44:49,931
Bye.

846
00:44:56,315 --> 00:44:57,783
Tid-Gift…

847
00:44:57,783 --> 00:44:59,217
I brought the money back.

848
00:44:59,217 --> 00:45:01,165
Back then I really needed it to pay off my soccer bet.

849
00:45:01,165 --> 00:45:03,165
I was being reckless, I know.

850
00:45:04,639 --> 00:45:07,639
Reckless or just brainless?

851
00:45:08,712 --> 00:45:11,707
Can we…make up?

852
00:45:11,707 --> 00:45:15,707
I mean, it looks like you’ve got all 32 body parts,

853
00:45:16,335 --> 00:45:20,336
but wait, maybe something’s missing…where’s your brain, huh?

854
00:45:21,053 --> 00:45:23,003
If you find it, try nourishing that

855
00:45:23,003 --> 00:45:24,579
instead of just your skin.

856
00:45:24,579 --> 00:45:25,579
You make me wanna puke.

857
00:45:29,546 --> 00:45:30,546
Tid-Gift.

858
00:45:30,733 --> 00:45:32,164
I’m here to make up.

859
00:45:32,164 --> 00:45:34,164
I finally got over my ex.

860
00:45:36,395 --> 00:45:40,187
Here we go again. You again? Hanging around hoping for pity.

861
00:45:40,187 --> 00:45:41,382
Are you okay?

862
00:45:41,382 --> 00:45:44,769
And your face, it’s like a perfect square.

863
00:45:44,769 --> 00:45:46,769
Side × side.

864
00:45:48,033 --> 00:45:51,224
That hurt…but I get it. Still, give me another chance.

865
00:45:51,224 --> 00:45:55,225
Hey! What’s going on?! Tid-Gift is my girlfriend.

866
00:45:55,935 --> 00:45:57,477
Tid-Gift, who the hell is this tall guy?

867
00:45:57,477 --> 00:45:58,545
Tall Guy?

868
00:45:58,545 --> 00:45:59,979
I’m her boyfriend too.

869
00:45:59,979 --> 00:46:03,363
Wait, what? Are you serious?

870
00:46:03,363 --> 00:46:06,669
Both of you shut up.

871
00:46:06,669 --> 00:46:07,669
Go fight each other back in the barnyard.

872
00:46:09,301 --> 00:46:13,301
I’m King. Her real boyfriend. Her first love.

873
00:46:15,088 --> 00:46:16,962
Flowers for you, darling.

874
00:46:16,962 --> 00:46:17,962
Thank you.

875
00:46:18,548 --> 00:46:20,548
See? Look who she chose.

876
00:46:25,007 --> 00:46:26,762
Why would you do this to me, babe?

877
00:46:26,762 --> 00:46:28,239
Don’t “babe” me.

878
00:46:28,239 --> 00:46:35,239
You’re turning into an invasive weed, useless and bad for the planet.

879
00:46:36,377 --> 00:46:39,125
But baby, you're my magical little bear.

880
00:46:39,125 --> 00:46:40,711
Did you forget Papa Bear already?

881
00:46:41,308 --> 00:46:44,221
Sure, my bear is magical…

882
00:46:44,221 --> 00:46:48,221
But you? You’re like a single knobby tamarind pod.

883
00:46:48,857 --> 00:46:51,725
You only saw the bear’s tail that day, you know.

884
00:46:51,725 --> 00:46:53,725
You haven’t seen the full Magical Bear Style in action.

885
00:46:55,362 --> 00:46:57,158
I love you, Tid-Gift, okay?

886
00:46:57,158 --> 00:47:00,351
Before you love someone else, try loving yourself first.

887
00:47:00,351 --> 00:47:02,544
Everyone hates you now.

888
00:47:02,544 --> 00:47:05,932
You thirsty? Want me to pour water or just toss gravel at you?

889
00:47:05,932 --> 00:47:07,237
You’re so freaking annoying.

890
00:47:07,237 --> 00:47:11,237
Look, just one tiny tamarind segment.

891
00:47:11,870 --> 00:47:12,899
Papa Bear...what the hell are you even saying?

892
00:47:12,899 --> 00:47:13,650
Yeah.

893
00:47:13,650 --> 00:47:15,358
Unbelievable, you’ve got no shame.

894
00:47:15,358 --> 00:47:16,553
What’s your problem, Shorty?

895
00:47:16,553 --> 00:47:18,028
Whoa, who are you calling short?

896
00:47:18,028 --> 00:47:19,303
You want a piece of me? C'mon!

897
00:47:19,303 --> 00:47:21,303
Tall Guy, get him!

898
00:47:25,086 --> 00:47:28,086
What a waste of time. I’m going to finish blow-drying my hair.

899
00:47:45,558 --> 00:47:48,585
Whoa, Kreetha, you packed your own meal today?

900
00:47:48,585 --> 00:47:50,585
Yeah. I'm trying to save money lately.

901
00:47:52,372 --> 00:47:55,722
And you're eating plain noodles? No sides?

902
00:47:55,722 --> 00:47:57,722
Side dish? Uh…fish sauce counts, right?

903
00:48:05,752 --> 00:48:06,752
Hey, Thomas.

904
00:48:09,178 --> 00:48:10,178
Tonight?

905
00:48:11,971 --> 00:48:12,971
I’m free.

906
00:48:15,601 --> 00:48:21,601
Tonight, I’ll give it to you hardcore, okay?

907
00:48:21,638 --> 00:48:23,498
Hold up, Chai.

908
00:48:23,498 --> 00:48:25,371
Aren’t we supposed to go out drinking tonight?

909
00:48:25,371 --> 00:48:28,243
I dressed up for this, okay? Show some respect!

910
00:48:28,243 --> 00:48:29,717
If you can schedule it, you can cancel it.

911
00:48:29,717 --> 00:48:31,069
You dressed up like that...

912
00:48:31,069 --> 00:48:32,695
then just go home and sleep.

913
00:48:32,695 --> 00:48:34,802
See you, ladies. See you, everyone.

914
00:48:34,802 --> 00:48:35,713
Whoa!

915
00:48:35,713 --> 00:48:37,101
My Thomas is waiting.

916
00:48:37,101 --> 00:48:39,370
You picked a guy again, ditching your friends again.

917
00:48:39,370 --> 00:48:41,162
What’s your heart made of, huh?

918
00:48:41,162 --> 00:48:42,662
Will you die if you go one day without sex?

919
00:48:43,291 --> 00:48:46,446
But it’s probably for the best. We should lay off the booze a bit.

920
00:48:46,746 --> 00:48:49,696
Try eating healthy for once and taking care of ourselves.

921
00:48:49,696 --> 00:48:51,444
Chaba, is that all you're eating?

922
00:48:51,444 --> 00:48:53,444
That’s more than enough. I’m stuffed.

923
00:48:57,949 --> 00:48:58,949
Chaba, what’s that?

924
00:49:01,538 --> 00:49:02,572
It's cheat day!

925
00:49:02,572 --> 00:49:04,048
Yeah, cheat day!

926
00:49:04,048 --> 00:49:04,722
Cheat day.

927
00:49:04,722 --> 00:49:05,993
It's okay.

928
00:49:05,993 --> 00:49:08,659
This is how it is. I try to eat...

929
00:49:08,659 --> 00:49:09,659
nutritious meals too.

930
00:49:11,319 --> 00:49:14,866
Hey, anyone interested in a desert lizard leather bag?

931
00:49:14,866 --> 00:49:18,213
This one’s from France.

932
00:49:18,213 --> 00:49:22,213
Retail price? Over two hundred grand.

933
00:49:22,968 --> 00:49:26,203
But today only, I’ll give you 50% off.

934
00:49:26,203 --> 00:49:26,877
Whoa.

935
00:49:26,877 --> 00:49:27,743
You interested, Kreetha?

936
00:49:27,743 --> 00:49:29,453
Buy it, Kreetha.

937
00:49:29,453 --> 00:49:30,722
Fifty percent off is a steal.

938
00:49:30,722 --> 00:49:33,350
Seriously, you could get it for your girlfriend. Do you have one?

939
00:49:33,350 --> 00:49:35,350
I can’t afford that, Sky.

940
00:49:37,384 --> 00:49:39,938
Okay, then how about this...

941
00:49:39,938 --> 00:49:41,481
Special friend price.

942
00:49:41,481 --> 00:49:42,481
Only 399.

943
00:49:43,027 --> 00:49:44,027
Try it first. It’s real leather.

944
00:49:44,255 --> 00:49:45,724
Go for it, Kreetha. Go for it.

945
00:49:45,724 --> 00:49:46,714
Feel it. The quality is amazing.

946
00:49:46,714 --> 00:49:48,067
It’s top-notch stuff. Seriously.

947
00:49:48,067 --> 00:49:50,472
The gold color attracts wealth.

948
00:49:50,472 --> 00:49:51,701
I don’t think so.

949
00:49:52,001 --> 00:49:52,947
Hey!

950
00:49:52,947 --> 00:49:53,854
What do you mean? It is real.

951
00:49:53,854 --> 00:49:55,125
How could it not be?

952
00:49:55,125 --> 00:49:56,953
I remember when she bought it.

953
00:49:56,953 --> 00:49:58,953
But this smells like 100% PU plastic.

954
00:50:00,986 --> 00:50:03,698
Oh, leather smells similar these days!

955
00:50:03,698 --> 00:50:06,084
Yeah! Maybe you're just imagining it.

956
00:50:06,084 --> 00:50:06,960
Totally.

957
00:50:06,960 --> 00:50:08,226
If you don’t believe me, want me to prove it?

958
00:50:08,226 --> 00:50:11,254
How are you gonna prove it? This came from a shop!

959
00:50:11,254 --> 00:50:13,602
If it’s real leather, it’s hard to burn.

960
00:50:13,602 --> 00:50:15,473
And even if it does catch fire, it just chars.

961
00:50:15,473 --> 00:50:16,103
Er...

962
00:50:16,103 --> 00:50:17,103
But if it’s fake...

963
00:50:23,734 --> 00:50:25,734
Holy shit, my bag!

964
00:50:26,845 --> 00:50:27,845
There's a big hole now!

965
00:50:28,514 --> 00:50:29,514
Sky, did you just scam me?

966
00:50:31,666 --> 00:50:34,456
Sky, let’s go to the restroom.

967
00:50:34,456 --> 00:50:35,404
I’ve got cramps.

968
00:50:35,404 --> 00:50:36,404
Right, period cramps!

969
00:50:37,591 --> 00:50:39,461
Why now of all times? Hurry up!

970
00:50:39,461 --> 00:50:40,461
Oww, it hurts!

971
00:50:41,166 --> 00:50:42,166
Hurry!

972
00:50:45,034 --> 00:50:46,034
Hey, free stuff!

973
00:50:46,945 --> 00:50:47,945
You really are poor, huh?

974
00:50:48,131 --> 00:50:50,131
Yeah, I admit it. I’m broke.

975
00:50:55,003 --> 00:50:56,270
Why does it taste so weird?

976
00:50:56,270 --> 00:50:56,979
What?

977
00:50:56,979 --> 00:50:57,979
Hmm?

978
00:50:58,521 --> 00:50:59,521
What is it?

979
00:51:00,236 --> 00:51:01,236
Oh, nothing. Never mind.

980
00:51:09,903 --> 00:51:10,903
How's All-New doing?

981
00:51:11,938 --> 00:51:12,938
He's amazing.

982
00:51:12,967 --> 00:51:15,108
He could do the exercide..

983
00:51:15,108 --> 00:51:15,705
Exercide, what?

984
00:51:16,105 --> 00:51:18,056
He could do the exercise and...

985
00:51:19,123 --> 00:51:20,123
Can you speak Korean?

986
00:51:27,101 --> 00:51:28,173
You're amazing too.

987
00:51:28,173 --> 00:51:28,960
Thank you.

988
00:51:28,960 --> 00:51:31,867
From now on, you follow my orders only.

989
00:51:31,867 --> 00:51:32,655
Okay, Mom.

990
00:51:32,655 --> 00:51:33,655
Stop calling me Mom!

991
00:51:36,593 --> 00:51:37,593
Okay!

992
00:51:38,026 --> 00:51:39,026
You gotta say not okay...

993
00:51:39,258 --> 00:51:40,758
Or else how am I gonna hit you?

994
00:51:41,529 --> 00:51:42,529
It's cool.

995
00:51:45,201 --> 00:51:46,201
How is it not cool?

996
00:51:48,514 --> 00:51:49,514
Okay, cut!

997
00:51:50,379 --> 00:51:51,379
Cut!

998
00:51:51,529 --> 00:51:53,029
I just kept going on.

999
00:51:53,682 --> 00:51:57,548
Do you wanna watch Magical Little Bear?

1000
00:51:57,548 --> 00:51:58,777
Do it again, the CD is upside down.

1001
00:51:58,777 --> 00:51:59,777
It's upside down.

1002
00:52:01,325 --> 00:52:02,325
No, don't hit your own head.

1003
00:52:03,272 --> 00:52:06,661
Let's take Little Bear to heaven.

1004
00:52:06,661 --> 00:52:09,161
Let's go, let's go build some international relations.

1005
00:52:10,319 --> 00:52:11,319
Let's go.

1006
00:52:12,707 --> 00:52:14,725
Let’s do a practice run first, just to see if it works.

1007
00:52:14,725 --> 00:52:15,725
Yeah, okay, sounds good.

1008
00:52:17,953 --> 00:52:18,253
Chaba.

1009
00:52:18,581 --> 00:52:18,881
Chaba.

1010
00:52:19,053 --> 00:52:19,353
Chaba.

1011
00:52:21,347 --> 00:52:23,498
Whoa, Sky, that’s terrifying.

1012
00:52:23,498 --> 00:52:24,498
Not that pose.

1013
00:52:25,732 --> 00:52:27,732
It looks like you’ve got a toothache.

1014
00:52:28,600 --> 00:52:29,600
Makes me wanna slap your mouth.

1015
00:52:29,745 --> 00:52:30,745
Come on, you try it.

1016
00:52:31,659 --> 00:52:32,659
No difference.

1017
00:52:33,813 --> 00:52:34,813
Now stick your tongue out.

1018
00:52:36,715 --> 00:52:37,715
Did someone choke you or something?

1019
00:52:38,311 --> 00:52:39,311
That pose of yours is really cute.

1020
00:52:39,657 --> 00:52:40,322
It's hideous.

1021
00:52:40,322 --> 00:52:41,322
Oh?

1022
00:52:49,752 --> 00:52:51,752
Well, we're friends, right? We're friends.

1023
00:52:54,658 --> 00:52:58,659
And after that, we started a business exporting psyllids.

1024
00:53:02,111 --> 00:53:03,339
What’s so funny?

1025
00:53:03,339 --> 00:53:04,484
Psyllids? Seriously?

1026
00:53:04,484 --> 00:53:05,484
Yes.

1027
00:53:07,314 --> 00:53:08,185
What?

1028
00:53:08,185 --> 00:53:09,975
How did you even come up with that, psyllids?

1029
00:53:09,975 --> 00:53:10,642
Have you ever seen one?

1030
00:53:10,642 --> 00:53:11,394
Nope.

1031
00:53:11,394 --> 00:53:12,182
They jump. Like, jump-jump.

1032
00:53:12,182 --> 00:53:14,182
That’s gotta be me.

1033
00:53:18,601 --> 00:53:19,601
It’s not coming out?

1034
00:53:22,194 --> 00:53:23,194
Hold on, just a sec.

1035
00:53:24,821 --> 00:53:25,821
Shit!

1036
00:53:26,650 --> 00:53:28,075
You’re flying on the same flight as us, aren’t you, Auntie?

1037
00:53:28,075 --> 00:53:30,151
I don’t even know which plane it is, dear.

1038
00:53:30,151 --> 00:53:31,940
Don’t worry, we’ll take care of you.

1039
00:53:31,940 --> 00:53:33,489
Sappé sattā...

1040
00:53:33,489 --> 00:53:34,868
Auntie...

1041
00:53:34,868 --> 00:53:36,487
Sorry, but you can’t chant out loud here.

1042
00:53:36,487 --> 00:53:37,072
Boy!

